  "description": "The Lost Coaster of Superstition Mountain is a wooden roller coaster at Indiana Beach in Monticello, Indiana, themed to that of a mine shaft.  It was the last coaster Custom Coasters International (CCI) finished (they had also started work on New Mexico Rattler at Cliff's Amusement Park but went bankrupt before they could finish it).  The ride is unusual as it has an elevator to raise the cars to the top of the track as opposed to the more traditional lift-hill.",
